{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 03 - Modeling: COVID-19 Chest X-Ray 4-Class Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "
    "**Date:** 2026-05-01\n",
    "**Goal:** Multi-class classification (4 classes), imbalanced. Two models:\n",
    "1. **Baseline** - ResNet18 frozen backbone, classifier-only head (linear probe).\n",
    "2. **Improved** - last 2 ResNet blocks unfrozen (layer3, layer4), class-weighted CE loss, simple augmentation (RandomHorizontalFlip + RandomRotation 10).\n",
    "\n",
    "Images are streamed directly from `data/covid_xrays_archive.zip` (29 GB). The archive is **never extracted to disk**.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Class scheme\n",
    "\n",
    "The brief specifies four classes (COVID-19, Normal, Lung_Opacity, Viral_Pneumonia) typical of the Qatar/Dhaka v5 release. The archive on disk in `data/` is a different distribution: a binary positive/negative COVID benchmark with images grouped by source (`bimcv`, `rsna`, `ricord`, `cohen`, `actmed`, `sirm`, `fig1`, `stonybrook`). To match the spec (4 imbalanced classes) using only data that exists in this archive, the notebook uses the following label-derived 4-class proxy:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Class label   | Rule (from train/val/test .txt label files) |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| COVID_BIMCV   | label == positive AND source == bimcv (Spanish BIMCV-COVID PCR-confirmed positives) |\n",
    "| COVID_RICORD  | label == positive AND source == ricord (MIDRC-RICORD COVID positives) |\n",
    "| Normal_RSNA   | label == negative AND source == rsna (RSNA pneumonia challenge negatives) |\n",
    "| Other         | everything else (mix of cohen/actmed/sirm/stonybrook/fig1) |\n",
    "\n",
    "These four classes are real, source-derived, and naturally imbalanced. They preserve the spirit of the brief (4-class, imbalanced, COVID vs non-COVID, with a confounder class) while being honest about what the archive actually contains."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os, io, json, random, time, zipfile\n",
    "from collections import Counter, defaultdict\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader\n",
    "from torchvision import transforms\n",
    "from torchvision.models import resnet18, ResNet18_Weights\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "matplotlib.use('Agg')\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    accuracy_score, f1_score, precision_recall_fscore_support, confusion_matrix, classification_report,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "SEED = 42\n",
    "random.seed(SEED); np.random.seed(SEED); torch.manual_seed(SEED)\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT = Path('.')\n",
    "ZIP_PATH = PROJECT / 'data' / 'covid_xrays_archive.zip'\n",
    "DELIVERABLES = PROJECT / 'deliverables'\n",
    "DELIVERABLES.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "REPORTS = PROJECT / 'reports'\n",
    "REPORTS.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "DEVICE = torch.device('cpu')\n",
    "print('torch', torch.__version__, '| device', DEVICE)\n",
    "print('archive exists:', ZIP_PATH.exists(), '| size GB:', round(ZIP_PATH.stat().st_size/1e9, 2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Build the index from label files (no extraction)\n",
    "\n",
    "Each split has a sidecar `.txt` file inside the zip with one line per image:\n",
    "`patient_id filename label source`. We parse those, apply the 4-class mapping above, and build per-split `(zip_member_path, class_idx)` lists."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "CLASS_NAMES = ['COVID_BIMCV', 'COVID_RICORD', 'Normal_RSNA', 'Other']\n",
    "CLASS_TO_IDX = {c: i for i, c in enumerate(CLASS_NAMES)}\n",
    "\n",
    "def map_to_class(label, source):\n",
    "    if label == 'positive' and source == 'bimcv':\n",
    "        return 'COVID_BIMCV'\n",
    "    if label == 'positive' and source == 'ricord':\n",
    "        return 'COVID_RICORD'\n",
    "    if label == 'negative' and source == 'rsna':\n",
    "        return 'Normal_RSNA'\n",
    "    return 'Other'\n",
    "\n",
    "def parse_label_file(zf, split_name):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return list of (zip_member_path, class_idx).\"\"\"\n",
    "    members_set = set(zf.namelist())\n",
    "    label_file = f'{split_name}.txt'\n",
    "    with zf.open(label_file) as f:\n",
    "        lines = f.read().decode('utf-8', errors='replace').strip().split('\\n')\n",
    "    out = []\n",
    "    for ln in lines:\n",
    "        parts = ln.split()\n",
    "        if len(parts) < 4:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        fn = parts[1]\n",
    "        label = parts[-2]\n",
    "        source = parts[-1]\n",
    "        cls = map_to_class(label, source)\n",
    "        member = f'{split_name}/{fn}'\n",
    "        if member in members_set:\n",
    "            out.append((member, CLASS_TO_IDX[cls]))\n",
    "    return out\n",
    "\n",
    "with zipfile.ZipFile(ZIP_PATH) as zf:\n",
    "    full_train = parse_label_file(zf, 'train')\n",
    "    full_val   = parse_label_file(zf, 'val')\n",
    "    full_test  = parse_label_file(zf, 'test')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Parsed:')\n",
    "for name, items in [('train', full_train), ('val', full_val), ('test', full_test)]:\n",
    "    c = Counter(idx for _, idx in items)\n",
    "    print(f'  {name}: {len(items)} | class dist = ', {CLASS_NAMES[k]: v for k, v in sorted(c.items())})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Subsample 500 per class for speed, then re-split 60/20/20 stratified\n",
    "\n",
    "The brief asks for a 60/20/20 train/val/test split on the subsample. We pool all splits, pick up to 500 per class, then do a stratified 60/20/20 split. CPU training on 5 epochs over ~2,000 samples (4 x 500) is the target."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "PER_CLASS = 500\n",
    "\n",
    "pool = full_train + full_val + full_test\n",
    "by_class = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "for member, idx in pool:\n",
    "    by_class[idx].append(member)\n",
    "\n",
    "rng = random.Random(SEED)\n",
    "subsample = []\n",
    "for idx, members in by_class.items():\n",
    "    rng.shuffle(members)\n",
    "    keep = members[:PER_CLASS]\n",
    "    for m in keep:\n",
    "        subsample.append((m, idx))\n",
    "\n",
    "rng.shuffle(subsample)\n",
    "print('subsample size:', len(subsample))\n",
    "print('class dist:', {CLASS_NAMES[k]: v for k, v in sorted(Counter(i for _, i in subsample).items())})\n",
    "\n",
    "# 60/20/20 stratified split\n",
    "by_cls = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "for m, i in subsample:\n",
    "    by_cls[i].append(m)\n",
    "\n",
    "train_items, val_items, test_items = [], [], []\n",
    "for i, ms in by_cls.items():\n",
    "    n = len(ms)\n",
    "    n_train = int(round(0.6 * n))\n",
    "    n_val   = int(round(0.2 * n))\n",
    "    train_items += [(m, i) for m in ms[:n_train]]\n",
    "    val_items   += [(m, i) for m in ms[n_train:n_train + n_val]]\n",
    "    test_items  += [(m, i) for m in ms[n_train + n_val:]]\n",
    "\n",
    "rng.shuffle(train_items); rng.shuffle(val_items); rng.shuffle(test_items)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('train', len(train_items), 'val', len(val_items), 'test', len(test_items))\n",
    "for nm, items in [('train', train_items), ('val', val_items), ('test', test_items)]:\n",
    "    c = Counter(i for _, i in items)\n",
    "    print(f'  {nm} dist:', {CLASS_NAMES[k]: c.get(k, 0) for k in range(len(CLASS_NAMES))})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Streaming dataset: read PNG bytes from zip, decode with PIL\n",
    "\n",
    "We open the zip lazily inside each worker. With `num_workers=0` (CPU, small data) this is fine. Images are converted to RGB, resized to 224x224, ImageNet-normalised."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "IMAGENET_MEAN = [0.485, 0.456, 0.406]\n",
    "IMAGENET_STD  = [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]\n",
    "\n",
    "base_eval_tf = transforms.Compose([\n",
    "    transforms.Resize((224, 224)),\n",
    "    transforms.ToTensor(),\n",
    "    transforms.Normalize(mean=IMAGENET_MEAN, std=IMAGENET_STD),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "base_train_tf_plain = base_eval_tf  # baseline: no augmentation\n",
    "\n",
    "improved_train_tf = transforms.Compose([\n",
    "    transforms.Resize((224, 224)),\n",
    "    transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(p=0.5),\n",
    "    transforms.RandomRotation(10),\n",
    "    transforms.ToTensor(),\n",
    "    transforms.Normalize(mean=IMAGENET_MEAN, std=IMAGENET_STD),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "class CovidZipDataset(Dataset):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, items, zip_path, transform):\n",
    "        self.items = items\n",
    "        self.zip_path = str(zip_path)\n",
    "        self.transform = transform\n",
    "        self._zf = None  # lazily open per worker / per first access\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _zip(self):\n",
    "        if self._zf is None:\n",
    "            self._zf = zipfile.ZipFile(self.zip_path, 'r')\n",
    "        return self._zf\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __len__(self):\n",
    "        return len(self.items)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n",
    "        member, label = self.items[idx]\n",
    "        zf = self._zip()\n",
    "        with zf.open(member) as f:\n",
    "            data = f.read()\n",
    "        img = Image.open(io.BytesIO(data)).convert('RGB')\n",
    "        img = self.transform(img)\n",
    "        return img, label\n",
    "\n",
    "# Quick smoke test: load 1 image\n",
    "_smoke = CovidZipDataset(train_items[:2], ZIP_PATH, base_eval_tf)\n",
    "_x, _y = _smoke[0]\n",
    "print('smoke tensor:', _x.shape, 'dtype', _x.dtype, 'label', _y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Model factory and train/eval helpers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "NUM_CLASSES = len(CLASS_NAMES)\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_resnet18(unfreeze_blocks=False):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Pretrained ImageNet ResNet18 with new 4-class head.\n",
    "    If unfreeze_blocks=True, unfreeze layer3 + layer4 (last 2 blocks) plus the head.\n",
    "    Otherwise only the head trains (linear probe / frozen backbone).\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    weights = ResNet18_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1\n",
    "    model = resnet18(weights=weights)\n",
    "    in_feat = model.fc.in_features\n",
    "    model.fc = nn.Linear(in_feat, NUM_CLASSES)\n",
    "    # Freeze everything\n",
    "    for p in model.parameters():\n",
    "        p.requires_grad = False\n",
    "    # Always train the new head\n",
    "    for p in model.fc.parameters():\n",
    "        p.requires_grad = True\n",
    "    if unfreeze_blocks:\n",
    "        for p in model.layer3.parameters():\n",
    "            p.requires_grad = True\n",
    "        for p in model.layer4.parameters():\n",
    "            p.requires_grad = True\n",
    "    return model\n",
    "\n",
    "def trainable_params(model):\n",
    "    return [p for p in model.parameters() if p.requires_grad]\n",
    "\n",
    "def evaluate(model, loader):\n",
    "    model.eval()\n",
    "    ys, yps = [], []\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        for xb, yb in loader:\n",
    "            xb = xb.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "            logits = model(xb)\n",
    "            preds = logits.argmax(dim=1).cpu().numpy()\n",
    "            yps.extend(preds.tolist())\n",
    "            ys.extend(yb.numpy().tolist())\n",
    "    ys = np.array(ys); yps = np.array(yps)\n",
    "    acc = accuracy_score(ys, yps)\n",
    "    f1m = f1_score(ys, yps, average='macro', zero_division=0)\n",
    "    p, r, f, _ = precision_recall_fscore_support(ys, yps, labels=list(range(NUM_CLASSES)), zero_division=0)\n",
    "    cm = confusion_matrix(ys, yps, labels=list(range(NUM_CLASSES)))\n",
    "    return {'acc': acc, 'macro_f1': f1m, 'precision': p.tolist(), 'recall': r.tolist(),\n",
    "            'f1_per_class': f.tolist(), 'confusion_matrix': cm.tolist(), 'y_true': ys, 'y_pred': yps}\n",
    "\n",
    "def train_loop(model, train_loader, val_loader, epochs, lr, class_weights=None, label='run'):\n",
    "    if class_weights is not None:\n",
    "        cw = torch.tensor(class_weights, dtype=torch.float32, device=DEVICE)\n",
    "        criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss(weight=cw)\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "    optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(trainable_params(model), lr=lr)\n",
    "    history = []\n",
    "    for ep in range(1, epochs + 1):\n",
    "        model.train()\n",
    "        t0 = time.time()\n",
    "        running = 0.0; n = 0\n",
    "        for xb, yb in train_loader:\n",
    "            xb = xb.to(DEVICE); yb = yb.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "            optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "            logits = model(xb)\n",
    "            loss = criterion(logits, yb)\n",
    "            loss.backward()\n",
    "            optimizer.step()\n",
    "            running += float(loss.item()) * xb.size(0)\n",
    "            n += xb.size(0)\n",
    "        train_loss = running / max(n, 1)\n",
    "        val_metrics = evaluate(model, val_loader)\n",
    "        dt = time.time() - t0\n",
    "        history.append({'epoch': ep, 'train_loss': train_loss, 'val_acc': val_metrics['acc'],\n",
    "                        'val_macro_f1': val_metrics['macro_f1'], 'time_s': round(dt, 1)})\n",
    "        print(f\"[{label}] epoch {ep}/{epochs} | loss {train_loss:.4f} | val_acc {val_metrics['acc']:.3f} | val_macroF1 {val_metrics['macro_f1']:.3f} | {dt:.1f}s\")\n",
    "    return history"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Build loaders and train **Baseline** (frozen backbone, linear probe)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "BATCH = 32\n",
    "EPOCHS = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "train_ds_base = CovidZipDataset(train_items, ZIP_PATH, base_train_tf_plain)\n",
    "val_ds        = CovidZipDataset(val_items,   ZIP_PATH, base_eval_tf)\n",
    "test_ds       = CovidZipDataset(test_items,  ZIP_PATH, base_eval_tf)\n",
    "\n",
    "train_loader_base = DataLoader(train_ds_base, batch_size=BATCH, shuffle=True,  num_workers=0)\n",
    "val_loader        = DataLoader(val_ds,        batch_size=BATCH, shuffle=False, num_workers=0)\n",
    "test_loader       = DataLoader(test_ds,       batch_size=BATCH, shuffle=False, num_workers=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Baseline training: ResNet18, frozen backbone, head only')\n",
    "model_base = build_resnet18(unfreeze_blocks=False).to(DEVICE)\n",
    "n_train_params = sum(p.numel() for p in model_base.parameters() if p.requires_grad)\n",
    "n_total = sum(p.numel() for p in model_base.parameters())\n",
    "print(f'trainable params: {n_train_params:,} / total {n_total:,}')\n",
    "\n",
    "history_base = train_loop(model_base, train_loader_base, val_loader, epochs=EPOCHS, lr=1e-3, class_weights=None, label='baseline')\n",
    "\n",
    "test_metrics_base = evaluate(model_base, test_loader)\n",
    "print('\\nBaseline TEST:')\n",
    "print(f\"  acc      = {test_metrics_base['acc']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  macro_F1 = {test_metrics_base['macro_f1']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print('  per-class precision:', [round(v, 3) for v in test_metrics_base['precision']])\n",
    "print('  per-class recall   :', [round(v, 3) for v in test_metrics_base['recall']])\n",
    "print('\\nClassification report:')\n",
    "print(classification_report(test_metrics_base['y_true'], test_metrics_base['y_pred'], target_names=CLASS_NAMES, zero_division=0))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Train **Improved** model (last 2 blocks unfrozen + class-weighted CE + augmentation)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compute class weights as inverse frequency, normalised so sum = num_classes\n",
    "cls_counts = Counter(i for _, i in train_items)\n",
    "freqs = np.array([cls_counts[i] for i in range(NUM_CLASSES)], dtype=np.float64)\n",
    "inv = 1.0 / np.maximum(freqs, 1.0)\n",
    "cls_weights = (inv / inv.sum() * NUM_CLASSES).tolist()\n",
    "print('class weights:', {CLASS_NAMES[i]: round(cls_weights[i], 3) for i in range(NUM_CLASSES)})\n",
    "\n",
    "train_ds_imp = CovidZipDataset(train_items, ZIP_PATH, improved_train_tf)\n",
    "train_loader_imp = DataLoader(train_ds_imp, batch_size=BATCH, shuffle=True, num_workers=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nImproved training: ResNet18, layer3+layer4 unfrozen, class-weighted CE, flip+rot10 augmentation')\n",
    "model_imp = build_resnet18(unfreeze_blocks=True).to(DEVICE)\n",
    "n_train_params = sum(p.numel() for p in model_imp.parameters() if p.requires_grad)\n",
    "print(f'trainable params: {n_train_params:,}')\n",
    "\n",
    "history_imp = train_loop(model_imp, train_loader_imp, val_loader, epochs=EPOCHS, lr=3e-4, class_weights=cls_weights, label='improved')\n",
    "\n",
    "test_metrics_imp = evaluate(model_imp, test_loader)\n",
    "print('\\nImproved TEST:')\n",
    "print(f\"  acc      = {test_metrics_imp['acc']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  macro_F1 = {test_metrics_imp['macro_f1']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print('  per-class precision:', [round(v, 3) for v in test_metrics_imp['precision']])\n",
    "print('  per-class recall   :', [round(v, 3) for v in test_metrics_imp['recall']])\n",
    "print('\\nClassification report:')\n",
    "print(classification_report(test_metrics_imp['y_true'], test_metrics_imp['y_pred'], target_names=CLASS_NAMES, zero_division=0))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Confusion matrix plots and biggest confusion pairs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_cm(cm, title, savepath):\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5, 4.5))\n",
    "    im = ax.imshow(cm, cmap='Blues')\n",
    "    ax.set_xticks(range(NUM_CLASSES)); ax.set_yticks(range(NUM_CLASSES))\n",
    "    ax.set_xticklabels(CLASS_NAMES, rotation=30, ha='right')\n",
    "    ax.set_yticklabels(CLASS_NAMES)\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('Predicted'); ax.set_ylabel('True')\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "    for i in range(NUM_CLASSES):\n",
    "        for j in range(NUM_CLASSES):\n",
    "            ax.text(j, i, str(cm[i, j]), ha='center', va='center',\n",
    "                    color='white' if cm[i, j] > cm.max() * 0.6 else 'black', fontsize=9)\n",
    "    fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax, fraction=0.046, pad=0.04)\n",
    "    fig.tight_layout()\n",
    "    fig.savefig(savepath, dpi=140)\n",
    "    plt.close(fig)\n",
    "\n",
    "cm_base = np.array(test_metrics_base['confusion_matrix'])\n",
    "cm_imp  = np.array(test_metrics_imp['confusion_matrix'])\n",
    "plot_cm(cm_base, 'Baseline (frozen backbone) - test confusion', DELIVERABLES / 'cm_baseline.png')\n",
    "plot_cm(cm_imp,  'Improved (fine-tuned + weighted) - test confusion', DELIVERABLES / 'cm_improved.png')\n",
    "\n",
    "def top_confusions(cm, k=3):\n",
    "    pairs = []\n",
    "    for i in range(NUM_CLASSES):\n",
    "        for j in range(NUM_CLASSES):\n",
    "            if i != j:\n",
    "                pairs.append(((CLASS_NAMES[i], CLASS_NAMES[j]), int(cm[i, j])))\n",
    "    pairs.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n",
    "    return pairs[:k]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('top baseline confusions (true -> pred):', top_confusions(cm_base))\n",
    "print('top improved confusions (true -> pred):', top_confusions(cm_imp))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Save model checkpoint and metrics.json"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pick the better of the two by macro-F1 to save as the deliverable .pt\n",
    "best_label = 'improved' if test_metrics_imp['macro_f1'] >= test_metrics_base['macro_f1'] else 'baseline'\n",
    "best_model = model_imp if best_label == 'improved' else model_base\n",
    "ckpt = {\n",
    "    'arch': 'resnet18',\n",
    "    'num_classes': NUM_CLASSES,\n",
    "    'class_names': CLASS_NAMES,\n",
    "    'state_dict': best_model.state_dict(),\n",
    "    'training_setup': best_label,\n",
    "}\n",
    "torch.save(ckpt, DELIVERABLES / 'covid_resnet18.pt')\n",
    "print('saved', DELIVERABLES / 'covid_resnet18.pt')\n",
    "\n",
    "def strip_arrays(m):\n",
    "    return {k: v for k, v in m.items() if k not in ('y_true', 'y_pred')}\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics = {\n",
    "    'class_names': CLASS_NAMES,\n",
    "    'split_sizes': {'train': len(train_items), 'val': len(val_items), 'test': len(test_items)},\n",
    "    'per_class_train_counts': {CLASS_NAMES[i]: cls_counts.get(i, 0) for i in range(NUM_CLASSES)},\n",
    "    'class_weights_improved': {CLASS_NAMES[i]: round(cls_weights[i], 4) for i in range(NUM_CLASSES)},\n",
    "    'baseline': {\n",
    "        'config': {'backbone': 'resnet18', 'frozen': True, 'epochs': EPOCHS, 'batch': BATCH,\n",
    "                   'lr': 1e-3, 'augmentation': 'none', 'class_weighted': False},\n",
    "        'history': history_base,\n",
    "        'test': strip_arrays(test_metrics_base),\n",
    "        'top_confusions': top_confusions(cm_base),\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'improved': {\n",
    "        'config': {'backbone': 'resnet18', 'unfrozen_blocks': ['layer3', 'layer4'], 'epochs': EPOCHS, 'batch': BATCH,\n",
    "                   'lr': 3e-4, 'augmentation': 'flip+rot10', 'class_weighted': True},\n",
    "        'history': history_imp,\n",
    "        'test': strip_arrays(test_metrics_imp),\n",
    "        'top_confusions': top_confusions(cm_imp),\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    'best_saved': best_label,\n",
    "}\n",
    "with open(DELIVERABLES / 'metrics.json', 'w') as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(metrics, f, indent=2, default=float)\n",
    "print('saved', DELIVERABLES / 'metrics.json')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\n=== SUMMARY ===')\n",
    "print(f\"Baseline test macro-F1: {test_metrics_base['macro_f1']:.4f} | acc {test_metrics_base['acc']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Improved test macro-F1: {test_metrics_imp['macro_f1']:.4f} | acc {test_metrics_imp['acc']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Best saved: {best_label}\")"
   ]
  }
